This dish reminded me of a special time on the Isle of Arran, Scotland. We rented a house, & had access to excellent salmon. Made up this recipe, based mainly on fact there weren't very many cooking pots in the house! Put baby spinach in a pan, add chopped shallot (1 or 2), chopped mushrooms if desired, 2 salmon fillets; then dust with salt, pepper & tarragon if desired; add a chopped scallion and/or 1 small diced tomato if you wish; then pour in a little white wine and cream (now I use the fat-free half & half), and some bits of butter, cut up. Cook gently for 15-20 minutes. Easy, forgiving and wonderful.

Rating: 4
Loved this dish--it couldn't be easier. The tarragon is the key to the wonderful flavor. Served it with brown rice for a simple, quick, lovely meal.

